p: A linear mixed model which included a random intercept by subject revealed overall significant effects of time (p<0.001), dose (p<0.001) and dose-time interaction (p<0.001) on both DHA and EPA plasma increases in dams. All treatment groups increased significantly more than the control group with AOCED administration (p<0.01) but plasma EPA increases between GD 28 and PPD 56 were more pronounced ( Fig 5B).
